data.title: Plentiful food … not so great on the margaritas
data.text:
Be warned, while the restaurant serves margaritas, do NOT order them here.  This is very good FOOD restaurant; order cerveza (36 ounce bottles), and enjoy more food than you can eat!

A colleague and I went into El Favorito, and we knew that (while it is a hole in the wall), it had to be great.  Every table was full, and we were the only gringos there.  If you want a well-prepared meal, hearty and plentiful food, and an authentic meal, go here. If you want the marketing hype of a pretentious advertising campaign … well, we can name a bunch of them.

I must also say that the prices that we paid were WELL under those charged by the slick advertising campaign locales.  So, very good food, quasi-attentive service, great prices, and abysmal margaritas … come here.  Hey, your hotel has a bar, right?  So get your margaritas there (just NOT at the Marriott … we had to teach the bartender how to make them, believe it or not).

data.title: Very nice staff, very bland food.
data.text:
Had a super burrito without rice. They forgot the guacamole (which sucked). Beef in the burrito was very bland and without a lot of flavor. 

Staff very nice.. gave me a nice, iced and salted mug for my Negro Modelo. 

So in sum, food could definitely be improved but the cleanliness, staff friendliness are first rate.

data.title: So Fresh
data.text: The food is so fresh, I really had an enjoyable meal.Their salsa bar has a large selection with free chips for an extra special dining experience. The counter is where one orders and the staff will bring food to the table, a very easy ordering system. The menu has a vast amount of food items which will be pleasing to most.

data.title: It's become a regular dining spot
data.text: The food is good and the staff is friendly although they speak very little English. It's exceptionally clean and very reasonably priced.
